    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"My personal Website"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"11cfccf7-00dd-5686-a05b-2f5bf8ce3c67","excerpt":"An eigenvector of a linear transformation is a vector (non-zero) that, when the linear transformation is applied to it, changes by only a scalar factor. This…","html":"<p>An eigenvector of a linear transformation is a vector (non-zero) that, when the linear transformation is applied to it, changes by only a scalar factor. This scalar factor is called eigenvalue.</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v} = \\lambda \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v}</annotation></semantics></math></span></div>\n<p>Where:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A</annotation></semantics></math></span></span>: Transformation Matrix</li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> \\overrightarrow{v}</annotation></semantics></math></span></span>: Eigenvector</li>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>λ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\lambda</annotation></semantics></math></span></span>: Eigenvalue</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To calculate the Eigenvectors we need to find the Eigenvalues first.</p>\n<h1 id=\"finding-the-eigenvalues\">Finding the Eigenvalues</h1>\n<p>From</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover><mo>→</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v} = \\lambda \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v} \\rightarrow A \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v}\n= \\lambda \\cdot I \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v}</annotation></semantics></math></span></div>\n<p>follows</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi>I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(A - \\lambda I) \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v} = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span></div>\n<p>which is only solvable if <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi>I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">det(A - \\lambda I) = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span></span> (characteristic equation).</p>\n<p>This means <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi>I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(A - \\lambda  I)</annotation></semantics></math></span></span> not invertible.</p>\n<p>The solution of the characteristic equation (<span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi>I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">det(A - \\lambda I) = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span></span>) are the eigenvalues.</p>\n<h1 id=\"eigenvectors\">Eigenvectors</h1>\n<p>There is one independent Eigenvector for each Eigenvalue.</p>\n<p>For each Eigenvalue solve</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi>I</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⋅</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(A - \\lambda I) \\cdot \\overrightarrow{v} = 0</annotation></semantics></math></span></div>\n<p>to get the corresponding Eigenvector <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">→</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\overrightarrow{v}</annotation></semantics></math></span></span> for a given Eigenvalue <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>λ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\lambda</annotation></semantics></math></span></span>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Eigenvectors and Eigenvalues","tags":null,"category":"Mathematics"},"headings":[{"depth":1,"value":"Finding the Eigenvalues"},{"depth":1,"value":"Eigenvectors"}]}},"pageContext":{"id":"11cfccf7-00dd-5686-a05b-2f5bf8ce3c67","previousPost":{"title":"Electrical Motors","slug":"/blog/electrical_motors"},"nextPost":{"title":"vim","slug":"/blog/vim"},"dates":{"created":1549728399,"modified":1647509701}}},
